item.description:
Please note New Day and Place!

Each year the Free State Project sponsors a week-long camp-out called Porcfest. As part of the week's activities, tours are offered of the various regions of New Hampshire for prospective movers.

The Seacoast tour will be Friday 6/26. Lunch will be at 12:15 at Newick's Lobster House in Dover, NH on Dover Point. This meetup is to allow Seacoast-area liberty lovers to meet prospective FSP movers and discuss their experiences in NH and the liberty movement here.

If you are a Seacoast-area friend of liberty, or thinking of moving to NH as part of the FSP, please join us for lunch.
item.how_to_find_us: We will be with the Porcfest bus tour.
